{
  "texts": [
    "SpatialLDA [33] introduces a spatial regularization term to the latent Dirichlet allocation model to encourage agreement between neighboring cells and outputs spatially aware topics.",
    "SpaGene [34] detects spatially variable genes on which non-negative matrix factorization is applied to generate latent factors.",
    "Furthermore, another key challenge in spatial transcriptomics analysis is dropout events and data sparsity, which is not yet taken into account by these existing methods.In this work, we developed an unsupervised spatially embedded deep representation (SEDR) method for learning a low-dimensional latent representation of gene expression embedded with spatial information.",
    "The SEDR model consists of two main components, a deep masked autoencoder network for learning latent representation and a variational graph autoencoder network for embedding spatial information.",
    "These two components are optimized jointly to generate a latent representation suited for spatial transcriptomics data analysis."
  ]
}